draw_string() - DERP OS man page

Name -------------------
draw_string() - draws a string to the user programs buffer.

Synopsis ---------------

#include "gl.h"

void draw_string( char* str, Uint32 x, Uint32 y, pixel p );

Description ------------

The draw_string function draws a string by calling get_pid to obtain the current
user program. It then draws the string by calling draw_character for every 
character in the string, it draws with color pixel(p) at ( x, y ).

Return Value -----------

No return value, side effects are a string drawn in the screen buffer.

